The paper focuses on software engineering practices related to code reuse and code quality, which falls under the scope of cs.SE (Software Engineering). The study also involves code clone detection and analysis, which can be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The issue of licensing conflicts and enforcement is relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the study involves surveys and analysis of user behavior on Stack Overflow, which can be considered as a form of social computing and falls under the scope of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
